A distressed Thobani Girha views the shot cows that were found piled in a heap Picture: Fredlin Adriaan A Uitenhage farmer, arrested in connection with the killing of 11 stray cattle on his farm outside the town, will return to court on 4 July. Carlo Andries Voigt, 37, appeared briefly in the Uitenhage Magistrate s Court on charges of malicious damage to property, discharging of a firearm and contravening the animal protection act. The case was postponed to July for further investigation and for the prosecution to get a copy of the police s ballistic report. Voigt, along with his attorney Andre Dorfling, left the court speedily after the case was adjourned. Read more in The Herald tomorrow. Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share